OL,3,CResidents asked to 'pay for service
OL,4,Cyou hope never to use'
OL,6,FUninsured patients have to pay #585
OL,7,Ffor an ambulance in Guernsey, while
OL,8,Fthe Flying Christine III marine
OL,9,Ftransfer costs #647 in Herm and #2,420
OL,10,Fin Sark.
OL,12,FThe Service is free at the point of
OL,13,Fuse for Alderney residents, as they
OL,14,Ffund it through their taxes.
OL,16,FChief Ambulance Officer Mark Mapp
OL,17,Fsays: "It's the odd position of asking
OL,18,Fyou to pay for a service you hope
OL,19,Fnever to use.
